### User Management Endpoints
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiVersion = v1
@accessToken = your_access_token_here
@userId = user_id_here

### 1. List All Users (Protected)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 2. Create New User (Protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "newuser",
    "email": "newuser@example.com",
    "password": "newpassword123",
    "full_name": "New User",
    "is_active": true
}

###

### 3. Get User by ID (Protected)
# Replace {{userId}} with actual user ID from previous responses
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 4. Update User (Protected)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "updateduser",
    "email": "updated@example.com",
    "full_name": "Updated User",
    "is_active": true
}

###

### 5. Partial Update User (Protected)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "full_name": "Partially Updated User"
}

###

### 6. Delete User (Protected)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/{{userId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 7. Get User Profile (Alternative endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 8. Test Unauthorized Access (No Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/

###

### 9. Test Invalid User ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/invalid-id
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 10. Test Create User with Invalid Data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/users/
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "",
    "email": "invalid-email",
    "password": "123"
}

###
